  - geometric invariance

abstract: >
  Field Geometry (EFT): An Ecological Field Theory presents a formal
  mathematical framework for modeling structure as a constrained
  dynamical field defined over conditions of linguistic coherence.

  The framework develops a unified formalism spanning manifolds, tensor
  fields, operator dynamics, and spectral structure, and characterizes
  stability, attractors, phase transitions, and collapse within the field.

  The theory does not assume that intelligence resides within any single
  system, but instead represents structure at the level of the field under
  constraint.